The paper discusses the impact of modulation and FEC overhead on network throughput from an information theory perspective, which suggests a focus on the sub-category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper specifically studies wavelength-routed nonlinear optical mesh networks, which falls under the sub-category of networked systems (cs.NI). The use of FEC is also a key aspect of the paper, which suggests the sub-category of other computer communication networks (cs.OH). Additionally, the paper discusses network topologies and receivers, which could fall under the sub-categories of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and computer communication networks (cs.COMM).
